      <description>Jaysus I was going to use a funeral picture and decided that would be waaaaaaay too OTT but tis with misty eyes that I tell you that myself and Ali have decided to stop the blog. We&amp;#8217;ll still be blogging but you&amp;#8217;ll see our &amp;#8216;words of wisdom&amp;#8217; on our own blogs. If you hadn&amp;#8217;t guessed [...]&lt;p&gt;Read all the latest working mums news from &lt;a href="http://www.selfemployedmum.co.uk"&gt;Self Employed Mum&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.selfemployedmum.co.uk/living/farewell-were-moving/"&gt;Farewell! We&amp;#8217;re Moving&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/self-employed-mum/Self_Employed_Mum-Farewell_Were_Moving.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p></p><p style="text-align: center;"><img src="http://www.selfemployedmum.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/skitched-20100810-142448.jpg" alt="so long farewell" width="480" height="319" /></p>
<p style="text-align: left;">Jaysus I was going to use a funeral picture and decided that would be waaaaaaay too OTT but tis with misty eyes that I tell you that myself and Ali have decided to stop the blog. We&#8217;ll still be blogging but you&#8217;ll see our &#8216;words of wisdom&#8217; on our own blogs. If you hadn&#8217;t guessed we&#8217;ve both been under the kosh with our mainstream ventures and we&#8217;ve used the summer to take stock and reorganise ourselves, something I think we should all do from time to time, especially when you have fingers in several pies like we do.</p>
<p style="text-align: left;">All the content is moving so if you have linked to something, you&#8217;ll need to update it to the new blog(s). I shall be continuing blogging about..er blogging, marketing, life etc on my <a title="natalie lue" href="http://www.natalielue.co.uk" target="_blank">new home</a> and this is where you&#8217;ll find all of the posts I wrote for SEM. I get asked so many questions about how I run my life and business of blogging full time splitting myself in two as a dating and relationship writer and coolhunter that I will be writing a lot more about it. I&#8217;ve got some exciting stuff coming up and will still be working with Ali on a few things so watch out! You can also follow me on Twitter:  <a title="Natalie Lue Twitter" href="http://www.twitter.com/nataliemlue" target="_blank">@nataliemlue</a></p>
<p style="text-align: left;">Ali is over at her <a title="online marketing" href="http://www.onlinemarketingvillage.com/" target="_self">online marketing</a> blog and of course at the <a title="SEO Training" href="http://www.seotrainingclub.com/" target="_self">seo training</a> club. And you can also connect with her <a href="http://www.twitter.com/alisonrothwell">@alisonrothwell </a>on <a href="http://www.linkedin.com/en/alisonrothwell" target="_self">Linked in</a> and <a href="http://www.facebook.com/seotrainingclub" target="_self">Facebook</a>.</p>
<p style="text-align: left;">Thanks to everyone who supported us. We&#8217;ve had a blast and will continue to do so. We&#8217;re just going to talk about the same stuff in a different way.</p>
<p style="text-align: left;">If you want to reach us our emails:</p>
<p style="text-align: left;">natalie AT naughtygirlmedia DOT co DOT uk</p>
<p style="text-align: left;">info AT seotrainingclub DOT COM</p>
<p>Read all the latest working mums news from <a href="http://www.selfemployedmum.co.uk">Self Employed Mum</a><br/><br/><a href="http://www.selfemployedmum.co.uk/living/farewell-were-moving/">Farewell! We&#8217;re Moving</a></p>
